The paper deals with the synthesis of dynamic textures using pre-trained convolutional networks. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image processing and analysis. The paper also deals with the generation of novel textures, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR). The use of pre-trained networks for object recognition and optical flow prediction suggests that the paper could also be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach using a user study, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
